"meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Anglo-Norman personal name <i>Ingeram</i> (Old French <i>Enguerran</i>, <i>Engerran</i>; ancient Germanic <i>Engelramnus</i>, <i>Ingelramnus</i>, <i>Engelrammus</i>, <i>Ingelrammus</i>), from the heroic name-element seen in such names as   Ingle   + <i>hrafn-</i> ‘raven’."],"variants":[{"name":"Inghram","meanings":["English: variant of   Ingram  ."]},{"name":"Ingle","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Ingel</i>, <i>Ingald</i>, <i>Ingold</i> (Old Norse <i>Ingialdr</i>, <i>Ingœld</i>, itself apparently borrowed from the Old English <i>Ingeld</i>, a name of ancient Germanic origin consisting of an intensive prefix <i>in-</i> + <i>geld-</i> ‘reward, forfeit’).","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Ingulf</i>, representing either Old Norse <i>Ingólfr</i>, <i>Ingulf</i> or its ancient Germanic cognate, <i>Ingenwulf</i>, introduced to England by the Normans; the first element is derived from an ancient Germanic heroic name, and the second is ‘wolf’. As a surname it either died out or was absorbed by <i>Ingle</i> and its variants.","Americanized form of German <b>Ingel</b>: from a short form of any of several ancient Germanic personal names formed with <i>Ing-</i> (see 1 above). The surname <i>Ingel</i> is very rare in Germany."]},{"name":"Ingrum","meanings":["English: variant of   Ingram  ."]},{"name":"Ingraham","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): of Norman origin, a variant of   Ingram  , influenced by   Graham  . This name is now more common in the US than in Britain."]},{"name":"Engram","meanings":["English: variant of   Ingram  . This form, recorded inthe 13th century, now appears to have died out in the British Isles."]}]},{"name":"Elen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Helen  , now also used outside Wales. It is identical with the Welsh vocabulary word <i>elen</i> ‘nymph’, but this is unlikely to be the origin. It is found in Welsh texts from an early period as an equivalent of <i>Helen</i>, for example as the name of the mother of Constantine, finder of the True Cross."],"variants":[{"name":"Elin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Elen ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elen Ingram was born about 1270, in Denbigh, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom as the daughter of Roger Ingram and Mrs Roger Ingram. She had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Gruffydd ap Owain ap Bleddyn."},"et":{"ABT    1270–Deceased":"umbes 1270–Surnud","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1265–Male":"1265–Surnud","1298–1374":"1298–1374","1299–Male":"1299–Surnud","1300–1360":"1300–1360","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1298":"1298","1265":"1265","1374":"1374","ABT    1270":"umbes 1270","1240":"1240","1360":"1360","before 1270":"enne 1270","1270":"1270","of Denbigh, Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbigh, Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales"},"fi":{"ABT    1270–Deceased":"noin 1270–Kuollut","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1265–Male":"1265–Kuollut","1298–1374":"1298–1374","1299–Male":"1299–Kuollut","1300–1360":"1300–1360","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1298":"1298","1265":"1265","1374":"1374","ABT    1270":"noin 1270","1240":"1240","1360":"1360","before 1270":"ennen vuotta 1270","1270":"1270","of Denbigh, Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbigh, Denbighshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales"},"fr":{"ABT    1270–Deceased":"environ 1270–Décédée","1270–Female":"1270–Décédée","1265–Male":"1265–Décédé","1298–1374":"1298–1374","1299–Male":"1299–Décédé","1300–1360":"1300–1360","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1300":"1300","1299":"1299","1298":"1298","1265":"1265","1374":"1374","ABT    1270":"environ 1270","1240":"1240","1360":"1360","before 1270":"avant 1270","1270":"1270","of Denbigh, Den